main event: Multiple unidentified flying objects were observed by military personnel and civilians in Key West, Florida, during July and August 1953.
interesting points: A retired military officer reported observing three round, white objects moving at approximately 600 to 800 mph., Observers described the objects as lacking navigation or clearance lights and producing no sound., The sightings were made during different weather conditions, but generally reported as hazy or overcast., No confirmation of additional air traffic was found during the times of the sightings., Observations were made by multiple witnesses, including military personnel and civilians.
